{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MPTxadSJhDVJVjhbVzuj6a","type":"tool_result","content":"<retrieval_status>success</retrieval_status>\n\n<task_id>wsov15lns</task_id>\n\n<task_type>local_workflow</task_type>\n\n<status>completed</status>\n\n<output>\n{\n  \"summary\": \"Generate a complete v2 dimension (spec -> art -> balanced enemies & items -> baked image maps -> overworld art -> QA) and flip it to in_review. v2-only: every encounter renders from a generated map image (coverage is asserted), so no runtime structures are registered. Opus does all design reasoning; thin Haiku shims run the deterministic generator scripts; gpt-image-2 makes the art.\",\n  \"agentCount\": 10,\n  \"logs\": [\n    \"Spec: \\\"The Escapement\\\" (slug=the-escapement, biome=rusted gear plains split by mainspring canyons and burning oil fens)\",\n    \"QA verdict: warn (9 flags)\",\n    \"Playable gate: passed (? enemies, ? items)\"\n  ],\n  \"result\": {\n    \"dimId\": 708,\n    \"name\": \"The Escapement\",\n    \"spec\": {\n      \"id\": 708,\n      \"name\": \"The Escapement\",\n      \"description\": \"A planet-sized machine cracked open to the sky, its interior a world of interlocked gears the size of towns, snapped mainsprings, and burning oil fens. Most of the works have seized with rust, but a few still grind through their thousand-year rotations. Everything ticks, slow and out of rhythm, tended by things that no longer know what they were built for.\",\n      \"palette\": {\n        \"primary\": \"#B08D3C\",\n        \"secondary\": \"#3A342B\",\n        \"accent\": \"#D9531E\"\n      },\n      \"mood\": \"Vast, patient, and mechanical. The grinding half-life of an engine that has outlived its purpose and keeps turning anyway.\",\n      \"biome\": \"rusted gear plains split by mainspring canyons and burning oil fens\",\n      \"droppedNoun\": \"\",\n      \"negatedNoun\": \"\",\n      \"enemyBatches\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Fodder\",\n          \"description\": \"cost 1-2, swarms\",\n          \"enemies\": [\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Cog Crawler\",\n              \"role\": \"weak fast melee that swarms in numbers\",\n              \"description\": \"A dog-sized brass automaton skittering on gear-tooth legs.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Ratchet Hound\",\n              \"role\": \"fast melee pack that closes distance quickly\",\n              \"description\": \"A four-legged iron automaton with a ratcheting, clicking gait.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Winder Acolyte\",\n              \"role\": \"fragile ranged that lobs oil flasks\",\n              \"description\": \"A robed cultist with a satchel of sloshing oil flasks.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Chime Bat\",\n              \"role\": \"flying melee that dives on soft targets\",\n              \"description\": \"A small clockwork bat with thin brass wings that ring in flight.\"\n            }\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Standard\",\n          \"description\": \"cost 3-4, core line\",\n          \"enemies\": [\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Winder Zealot\",\n              \"role\": \"sturdy melee that swings a heavy spanner\",\n              \"description\": \"A cultist in oil-stained robes hefting an iron cranking-spanner.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Watchman\",\n              \"role\": \"durable frontline melee with a halberd\",\n              \"description\": \"A brass humanoid automaton standing guard with a long halberd.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Rivet Gunner\",\n              \"role\": \"ranged attacker that fires rivets in bursts\",\n              \"description\": \"A squat automaton with a clattering rivet-cannon for an arm.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Brass Guard\",\n              \"role\": \"armored blocker that shields nearby allies\",\n              \"description\": \"A broad iron automaton behind a riveted tower shield.\"\n            }\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Elite\",\n          \"description\": \"cost 5-6, threats\",\n          \"enemies\": [\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Winder Priest\",\n              \"role\": \"support that heals and hastens cult allies\",\n              \"description\": \"A tall cultist turning a great brass key set into its own back.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Piston Golem\",\n              \"role\": \"slow heavy bruiser with crushing single hits\",\n              \"description\": \"A hulking automaton with massive piston-driven arms.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Steam Lancer\",\n              \"role\": \"fast charger that lances across the field\",\n              \"description\": \"A sleek automaton balanced on one wheel, trailing steam and couching a lance.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Sweeper\",\n              \"role\": \"melee that sweeps and damages several tiles at once\",\n              \"description\": \"A wide, low engine dragging a spinning blade arm that throws sparks.\"\n            }\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Boss\",\n          \"description\": \"cost 7+, set-piece\",\n          \"enemies\": [\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Shepherd Engine\",\n              \"role\": \"huge high-HP boss that sweeps whole rows as debris\",\n              \"description\": \"A mountain-tall walking engine with plow-arms that clear everything before it.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Foreman\",\n              \"role\": \"boss that summons and repairs automatons\",\n              \"description\": \"A many-armed overseer automaton clutching stone work-order tablets.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Winder Prophet\",\n              \"role\": \"boss that sacrifices minions to heal itself and buffs the cult\",\n              \"description\": \"A gaunt cultist crowned in gears, feeding acolytes to a churning spring.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"name\": \"Coil Colossus\",\n              \"role\": \"long-range boss that lashes with spring-steel whips\",\n              \"description\": \"A giant assembled from snapped mainsprings, uncoiling steel lashes.\"\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      ],\n      \"items\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Brass Sword\",\n          \"type\": \"sword\",\n          \"rarity\": \"common\",\n          \"description\": \"A short blade cast from salvaged brass.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Ratchet Saber\",\n          \"type\": \"sword\",\n          \"rarity\": \"uncommon\",\n          \"description\": \"A saw-toothed blade that grinds through armor.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Cinder Sword\",\n          \"type\": \"sword\",\n          \"rarity\": \"uncommon\",\n          \"description\": \"A blade kept burning in oil-fen flame.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Mainspring Blade\",\n          \"type\": \"sword\",\n          \"rarity\": \"rare\",\n          \"description\": \"A whip-thin blade of coiled spring-steel.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Iron Spear\",\n          \"type\": \"spear\",\n          \"rarity\": \"common\",\n          \"description\": \"A plain iron-tipped shaft.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Piston Lance\",\n          \"type\": \"spear\",\n          \"rarity\": \"uncommon\",\n          \"description\": \"A spring-driven head that punches forward on the thrust.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Hook Pike\",\n          \"type\": \"spear\",\n          \"rarity\": \"rare\",\n          \"description\": \"A barbed head on a winch that drags enemies in.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Rivet Bow\",\n          \"type\": \"bow\",\n          \"rarity\": \"common\",\n          \"description\": \"A crossbow that fires salvaged rivets.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Coil Crossbow\",\n          \"type\": \"bow\",\n          \"rarity\": \"uncommon\",\n          \"description\": \"A wound-spring bow with a brutal draw.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Spark Bow\",\n          \"type\": \"bow\",\n          \"rarity\": \"rare\",\n          \"description\": \"Looses arrows trailing oil-fire.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Coil Staff\",\n          \"type\": \"staff\",\n          \"rarity\": \"common\",\n          \"description\": \"Discharges stored spring-force in a shove.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Chime Rod\",\n          \"type\": \"staff\",\n          \"rarity\": \"uncommon\",\n          \"description\": \"Rings out a concussive wave.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Arc Rod\",\n          \"type\": \"staff\",\n          \"rarity\": \"rare\",\n          \"description\": \"Throws crackling sparks at range.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Gear Maul\",\n          \"type\": \"two-handed\",\n          \"rarity\": \"common\",\n          \"description\": \"A town-gear tooth mounted on a heavy haft.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Flywheel Axe\",\n          \"type\": \"two-handed\",\n          \"rarity\": \"uncommon\",\n          \"description\": \"A spinning weighted axe head that keeps its momentum.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"Piston Hammer\",\n          \"type\": \"two-handed\",\n          \"rarity\": \"rare\",\n          \"description\": \"A steam-driven maul that slams for enormous force.\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"verdict\": {\n      \"verdict\": \"warn\",\n      \"summary\": {\n        \"dimensionName\": \"The Escapement\",\n        \"overallExpertSoloWin\": 53.5,\n        \"overallDumbSoloWin\": 13.4,\n        \"overallSkillGap\": 40.1,\n        \"dim0DumbBaseline\": 0,\n        \"flagCount\": 9\n      },\n      \"flags\": [\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"winder-acolyte\",\n          \"issue\": \"expert-win-high\",\n          \"value\": 100\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"winder-acolyte\",\n          \"issue\": \"dumb-win-high\",\n          \"value\": 33.3\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"chime-bat\",\n          \"issue\": \"dumb-win-high\",\n          \"value\": 22.2\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"watchman\",\n          \"issue\": \"dumb-win-high\",\n          \"value\": 33.3\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"brass-guard\",\n          \"issue\": \"dumb-win-high\",\n          \"value\": 33.3\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"winder-priest\",\n          \"issue\": \"dumb-win-high\",\n          \"value\": 33.3\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"foreman\",\n          \"issue\": \"expert-win-low\",\n          \"value\": 25.9\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"winder-prophet\",\n          \"issue\": \"expert-win-low\",\n          \"value\": 29.6\n        },\n        {\n          \"enemy\": \"coil-colossus\",\n          \"issue\": \"expert-win-low\",\n          \"value\": 22.2\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"playUrl\": \"?dim=708\",\n    \"assetDirs\": [\n      \"/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/server/sprites/enemies/dimension-708\",\n      \"/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/public/sprites/items/dimension-708\",\n      \"/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/public/sprites/map-objects/dimension-708\",\n      \"/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/public/sprites/map-decorations/dimension-708\",\n      \"/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/public/sprites/maps/dimension-708\",\n      \"/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/dimension-generator/diffusion-bundles/the-escapement\"\n    ],\n    \"notes\": \"Status flipped to in_review. Shared db: /home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/server/hex-discovery.sqlite.\\n\\nArt: Successfully generated all 8 diffusion bundles for The Escapement (dimension 708) via gpt-image-2 in 63.4 seconds. Sprites were extracted to four primary directories: /home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/public/sprites/map-objects/dimension-708 (25 sprites), /home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/public/sprites/map-decorations/dimension-708 (36 sprites), /home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/public/sprites/items/dimension-708 (16 items), and /home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/server/sprites/enemies/dimension-708 (enemy sprites from fodder/standard/elite/boss bundles with 16 sprites per tier). The background bundle was copied, and all extraction completed without errors.\\n\\nMaps: 25 maps, coverage OK — STEP 1: Generated dimension reference + 24 encounter maps + collision masks (122.1s). STEP 2: Verified coverage OK - all 14 encounter types have maps. STEP 3: Uploaded 25 PNG map assets to s3://schoolland-tbg-maps/sprites/maps/dimension-708/\\n\\nOverworld: Dimension 708 (The Escapement): registered 0 structures (v2 decorations-only)\\n  backgroundPath:      sprites/map-objects/dimension-708/background.png\\n  hexDecorationsPath:  sprites/map-decorations/dimension-708\\n\\nEnemy agent: Locked in. Iteration 3 held the aggregate perfectly and fixed the last outlier: `coil-colossus` party-win rose 22 → 66.7 (now matching dim-0's stone-golem), while its solo stays boss-appropriately hard.\\n\\n## Final result — dimension 708 \\\"The Escapement\\\"\\n\\n**Aggregate vs dim-0 gold standard (bullseye):**\\n| metric | dim-708 | dim-0 |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| expert solo win | 53.5 | 54.2 |\\n| dumb solo win | 13.4 | 13.4 |\\n| skill gap | 40.1 | 40.8 |\\n\\nDumb-solo matches dim-0 exactly (no runaway faceroll), skill gap is healthy, and the per-enemy spread mirrors dim-0's distribution (the handful sitting at 33.3 dumb-win line up with goblin-archer/shield). Bosses are hard solo, beatable by a coordinated party.\\n\\n**Roster by tier (16 enemies):**\\n- **Fodder:** `cog-crawler` (cheap melee swarm), `ratchet-hound` (fast lunging pack), `winder-acolyte` (fragile ranged — oil-flask projectile + `Burning Slick` damage zone), `chime-bat` (flying dive)\\n- **Standard:** `winder-zealot` (swing + heavy overhead), `watchman` (halberd sweep + reach thrust that applies `slowed`), `rivet-gunner` (rivet burst + suppressive cone applying `suppressed`), `brass-guard` (`Tower Shield` barrier + `Shielding Line` ally-barrier zone + bash)\\n- **Elite:** `winder-priest` (heal zone + ward barrier-zone + `winded` strike), `piston-golem` (slow, huge single hits — model skill-gap enemy), `steam-lancer` (fast charge with lungeThrough), `sweeper` (wide 180° sweep + `Spark Spray` damage zone)\\n- **Boss:** `shepherd-engine` (row-clearing plow + grinding `slowed` advance, onDeath→cog-crawler), `foreman` (`Repair Field` heal zone + rivet volley, onDeath→ratchet-hound), `winder-prophet` (heal + fervor barrier zones + `suppressed` lash, onDeath→winder-acolyte), `coil-colossus` (200-reach lash w/ `pull` + `slowed` snap, onDeath→chime-bat)\\n\\n**Ability-kind variety (not a flat all-attack roster):** barrier on brass-guard; damage zones (acolyte, sweeper), heal zones (priest, foreman, prophet), and addBarrier zones (brass-guard, priest, prophet); status debuffs `slowed`/`suppressed`/`winded` thread the \\\"engine winding down\\\" theme through watchman, rivet-gunner, priest, prophet, shepherd, coil. Elites/bosses carry 3 abilities; fodder stay lean at 2.\\n\\n**What I tuned and why:**\\n- **Iteration 1** ran too easy (expert 63 / dumb 22.7): fodder and ranged units were undertuned, letting the \\\"run-in-and-attack\\\" dumb baseline win far more than in dim-0. `winder-acolyte` (dumb 74) and `rivet-gunner` (dumb 44) were the outliers.\\n- **Iteration 2 (deliberate push):** raised damage/HP across fodder + standard + the two easy elites — mostly dodgeable, telegraphed, or zone/debuff damage that punishes the no-dodge/no-block dumb baseline harder than experts. This widened the skill gap while dropping dumb-win. It landed dead-on the dim-0 band (53.5 / 13.4 / 40.1).\\n- **Iteration 3 (lock-in):** single targeted fix — `coil-colossus` (hp 330→305, lash 40→36) to pull it into the dim-0 boss band; party-win recovered to 66.7 with no aggregate drift.\\n\\nAll changes were stat/lethality tuning within existing roles — no shapes, strategies, or identities changed — so every enemy still matches its spec description and existing art; no visual re-evaluation needed.\\n\\nRoster authoring file: `/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/dimension-generator/tmp-dim708-roster.ts`\\nBalance report: `/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/balance-report-dim-708.json`\\n\\nItem agent: All 16 weapons are in the DB and balanced. Final report below.\\n\\n**Dimension 708 \\\"The Escapement\\\" — 16 weapons, all balanced (final test: no worse-than-baseline, no rarity-inversion flags).**\\n\\nFinal ranking tracks rarity cleanly: rares 142–161, uncommons 116–142, commons 109–124, all above the 105 baseline.\\n\\n**Weapon IDs (all `d708-` prefixed):**\\n- Swords: `d708-brass-sword` (C), `d708-ratchet-saber` (U, saw-suppress debuff), `d708-cinder-sword` (U, spammable fire nova + lunge), `d708-mainspring-blade` (R, long-reach + spring lunge)\\n- Spears: `d708-iron-spear` (C), `d708-piston-lance` (U, wall-slam + recoil spacing), `d708-hook-pike` (R, winch pull)\\n- Bows: `d708-rivet-bow` (C), `d708-coil-crossbow` (U, heavy/piercing bolts), `d708-spark-bow` (R, ranged AoE firebrand)\\n- Staves: `d708-coil-staff` (C, shove + wall-slam), `d708-chime-rod` (U, concussive AoE + winded), `d708-arc-rod` (R, ranged bolt/AoE + suppress)\\n- Two-handed: `d708-gear-maul` (C), `d708-flywheel-axe` (U, 240° sweep + momentum lunge), `d708-piston-hammer` (R, top-end slam + wall-slam)\\n\\n**What I tuned and why (5 iterations, binary-search style):**\\n1. **Ranged over-dominance (biggest structural issue):** the test's score = winRate + avgHp double-rewards not getting hit, so bows/ranged staves inflated avgHp — `rivet-bow` (common) and `coil-crossbow` (uncommon) initially outscored rares. Fixed by cutting ranged damage hard (e.g. Heavy Bolt 26→17, Coil Bolt 30→21, Arc Bolt 30→26), trading raw damage for their inherent safety so range is a real cost, not free power.\\n2. **Melee / 2H underperformance:** two-handers lose the shield the sim keeps for 1H weapons, and short-range staves were under-tuned. Boosted their damage/shape (Gear Smash to 41, Flywheel Spin to 42, Spring Shove to 27, Whipcrack Arc to 38) so they clear baseline and their tiers.\\n3. **chime-rod:** its knockback (35) on a self-centered AoE was shoving enemies out of its own range — reworked to a damage-forward nuke (22→32 dmg, knockback 35→20).\\n4. **cinder-sword** (stubbornly weak despite two damage buffs): the cause was engagement, not damage — a utility-less melee sword that died approaching kiters. Mechanical fixes converted where stats didn't: made Cinder Burst a red1 spammable fire nova (AoE identity) and gave Flame Lash a lunge to close gaps, lifting it from 104→122.\\n\\nWorking definitions live at `/tmp/d708/weapons.ts` (source of truth for the emitted JSON). Note: `/tmp/d708` initially contained 14 stale weapon JSONs from a prior attempt that my upsert loop swept into the DB; I deleted those rows so dim 708 holds exactly these 16.\"\n  },\n  \"workflowProgress\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"workflow_phase\",\n      \"index\": 1,\n      \"title\": \"Spec\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"workflow_phase\",\n      \"index\": 2,\n      \"title\": \"Generate\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"workflow_phase\",\n      \"index\": 3,\n      \"title\": \"Overworld\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"workflow_phase\",\n      \"index\": 4,\n      \"title\": \"QA\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"workflow_phase\",\n      \"index\": 5,\n      \"title\": \"Stage\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"workflow_agent\",\n      \"index\": 1,\n   