exDecorationsPath:  sprites/map-decorations/dimension-708\\n\\nEnemy agent: Locked in. Iteration 3 held the aggregate perfectly and fixed the last outlier: `coil-colossus` party-win rose 22 → 66.7 (now matching dim-0's stone-golem), while its solo stays boss-appropriately hard.\\n\\n## Final result — dimension 708 \\\"The Escapement\\\"\\n\\n**Aggregate vs dim-0 gold standard (bullseye):**\\n| metric | dim-708 | dim-0 |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| expert solo win | 53.5 | 54.2 |\\n| dumb solo win | 13.4 | 13.4 |\\n| skill gap | 40.1 | 40.8 |\\n\\nDumb-solo matches dim-0 exactly (no runaway faceroll), skill gap is healthy, and the per-enemy spread mirrors dim-0's distribution (the handful sitting at 33.3 dumb-win line up with goblin-archer/shield). Bosses are hard solo, beatable by a coordinated party.\\n\\n**Roster by tier (16 enemies):**\\n- **Fodder:** `cog-crawler` (cheap melee swarm), `ratchet-hound` (fast lunging pack), `winder-acolyte` (fragile ranged — oil-flask projectile + `Burning Slick` damage zone), `chime-bat` (flying dive)\\n- **Standard:** `winder-zealot` (swing + heavy overhead), `watchman` (halberd sweep + reach thrust that applies `slowed`), `rivet-gunner` (rivet burst + suppressive cone applying `suppressed`), `brass-guard` (`Tower Shield` barrier + `Shielding Line` ally-barrier zone + bash)\\n- **Elite:** `winder-priest` (heal zone + ward barrier-zone + `winded` strike), `piston-golem` (slow, huge single hits — model skill-gap enemy), `steam-lancer` (fast charge with lungeThrough), `sweeper` (wide 180° sweep + `Spark Spray` damage zone)\\n- **Boss:** `shepherd-engine` (row-clearing plow + grinding `slowed` advance, onDeath→cog-crawler), `foreman` (`Repair Field` heal zone + rivet volley, onDeath→ratchet-hound), `winder-prophet` (heal + fervor barrier zones + `suppressed` lash, onDeath→winder-acolyte), `coil-colossus` (200-reach lash w/ `pull` + `slowed` snap, onDeath→chime-bat)\\n\\n**Ability-kind variety (not a flat all-attack roster):** barrier on brass-guard; damage zones (acolyte, sweeper), heal zones (priest, foreman, prophet), and addBarrier zones (brass-guard, priest, prophet); status debuffs `slowed`/`suppressed`/`winded` thread the \\\"engine winding down\\\" theme through watchman, rivet-gunner, priest, prophet, shepherd, coil. Elites/bosses carry 3 abilities; fodder stay lean at 2.\\n\\n**What I tuned and why:**\\n- **Iteration 1** ran too easy (expert 63 / dumb 22.7): fodder and ranged units were undertuned, letting the \\\"run-in-and-attack\\\" dumb baseline win far more than in dim-0. `winder-acolyte` (dumb 74) and `rivet-gunner` (dumb 44) were the outliers.\\n- **Iteration 2 (deliberate push):** raised damage/HP across fodder + standard + the two easy elites — mostly dodgeable, telegraphed, or zone/debuff damage that punishes the no-dodge/no-block dumb baseline harder than experts. This widened the skill gap while dropping dumb-win. It landed dead-on the dim-0 band (53.5 / 13.4 / 40.1).\\n- **Iteration 3 (lock-in):** single targeted fix — `coil-colossus` (hp 330→305, lash 40→36) to pull it into the dim-0 boss band; party-win recovered to 66.7 with no aggregate drift.\\n\\nAll changes were stat/lethality tuning within existing roles — no shapes, strategies, or identities changed — so every enemy still matches its spec description and existing art; no visual re-evaluation needed.\\n\\nRoster authoring file: `/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/dimension-generator/tmp-dim708-roster.ts`\\nBalance report: `/home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/balance-report-dim-708.json`\\n\\nItem agent: All 16 weapons are in the DB and balanced. Final report below.\\n\\n**Dimension 708 \\\"The Escapement\\\" — 16 weapons, all balanced (final test: no worse-than-baseline, no rarity-inversion flags).**\\n\\nFinal ranking tracks rarity cleanly: rares 142–161, uncommons 116–142, commons 109–124, all above the 105 baseline.\\n\\n**Weapon IDs (all `d708-` prefixed):**\\n- Swords: `d708-brass-sword` (C), `d708-ratchet-saber` (U, saw-suppress debuff), `d708-cinder-sword` (U, spammable fire nova + lunge), `d708-mainspring-blade` (R, long-reach + spring lunge)\\n- Spears: `d708-iron-spear` (C), `d708-piston-lance` (U, wall-slam + recoil spacing), `d708-hook-pike` (R, winch pull)\\n- Bows: `d708-rivet-bow` (C), `d708-coil-crossbow` (U, heavy/piercing bolts), `d708-spark-bow` (R, ranged AoE firebrand)\\n- Staves: `d708-coil-staff` (C, shove + wall-slam), `d708-chime-rod` (U, concussive AoE + winded), `d708-arc-rod` (R, ranged bolt/AoE + suppress)\\n- Two-handed: `d708-gear-maul` (C), `d708-flywheel-axe` (U, 240° sweep + momentum lunge), `d708-piston-hammer` (R, top-end slam + wall-slam)\\n\\n**What I tuned and why (5 iterations, binary-search style):**\\n1. **Ranged over-dominance (biggest structural issue):** the test's score = winRate + avgHp double-rewards not getting hit, so bows/ranged staves inflated avgHp — `rivet-bow` (common) and `coil-crossbow` (uncommon) initially outscored rares. Fixed by cutting ranged damage hard (e.g. Heavy Bolt 26→17, Coil Bolt 30→21, Arc Bolt 30→26), trading raw damage for their inherent safety so range is a real cost, not free power.\\n2. **Melee / 2H underperformance:** two-handers lose the shield the sim keeps for 1H weapons, and short-range staves were under-tuned. Boosted their damage/shape (Gear Smash to 41, Flywheel Spin to 42, Spring Shove to 27, Whipcrack Arc to 38) so they clear baseline and their tiers.\\n3. **chime-rod:** its knockback (35) on a self-centered AoE was shoving enemies out of its own range — reworked to a damage-forward nuke (22→32 dmg, knockback 35→20).\\n4. **cinder-sword** (stubbornly weak despite two damage buffs): the cause was engagement, not damage — a utility-less melee sword that died approaching kiters. Mechanical fixes converted where stats didn't: made Cinder Burst a red1 spammable fire nova (AoE identity) and gave Flame Lash a lunge to close gaps, lifting it from 104→122.\\n\\nWorking definitions live at `/tmp/d708/weapons.t