6 items), and `server/sprites/enemies/dimension-708` (16 sprites per tier across fodder/standard/elite/boss). The background bundle was copied, and all extraction completed without errors.\n>\n> **Maps:** 25 maps, coverage OK — Generated dimension reference + 24 encounter maps + collision masks (122.1s). Verified coverage OK, all 14 encounter types have maps. Uploaded 25 PNG map assets to `s3://schoolland-tbg-maps/sprites/maps/dimension-708/`\n>\n> **Overworld:** Dimension 708 (The Escapement): registered 0 structures (v2 decorations-only). backgroundPath: `sprites/map-objects/dimension-708/background.png`, hexDecorationsPath: `sprites/map-decorations/dimension-708`\n>\n> **Enemy agent:** Locked in after 3 iterations. Aggregate vs dim-0 gold standard: expert solo win 53.5 (dim-0: 54.2), dumb solo win 13.4 (dim-0: 13.4), skill gap 40.1 (dim-0: 40.8). Iteration 1 ran too easy (expert 63 / dumb 22.7); iteration 2 raised damage/HP across fodder, standard, and the two easy elites, landing dead-on the dim-0 band; iteration 3 was a single targeted fix to `coil-colossus` (hp 330→305, lash 40→36), whose party-win recovered 22 → 66.7 with no aggregate drift. All changes were stat/lethality tuning within existing roles — no shapes, strategies, or identities changed, so no visual re-evaluation needed. Roster file: `dimension-generator/tmp-dim708-roster.ts`. Balance report: `balance-report-dim-708.json`.\n>\n> **Item agent:** All 16 weapons in the DB and balanced (final test: no worse-than-baseline, no rarity-inversion flags). Final ranking tracks rarity cleanly: rares 142–161, uncommons 116–142, commons 109–124, all above the 105 baseline. Five iterations. The biggest structural issue was ranged over-dominance — the test's score (winRate + avgHp) double-rewards not getting hit, so bows/ranged staves inflated avgHp and `rivet-bow` (common) outscored rares; fixed by cutting ranged damage hard. Two-handers and short-range staves were under-tuned and got boosted. `chime-rod`'s knoc